cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.CE

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with network analysis and clustering in the context of U.S. airline networks.
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a likely category as the paper proposes a new measure and discusses its runtime performance.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper gives analytic formulae for the new measure and discusses its theoretical properties and limitations.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper uses the new measure to provide insight into changes in network structure over time.
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is relevant as the paper applies network analysis to a real-world problem in the domain of transportation.
